            <div class="jumbotron">
                <h1>Rooftop Building</h1>
                <p>An interdisciplinary group of ca. 40 students of the UdK Berlin and the TU Berlin planned, designed, and constructed
                  a small PlusEnergy living unit as part of the international competition Solar Decathlon Europe (SDE) 2014 in Versailles (France).
                  In accordance with the theme of the competition "urban densification", it was conceived
                  to be able to be placed on the roof of a pre-existing building, e.g. a Gr√ºnderzeit building in Berlin.</p>

                  <div class="col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
                      <div class="thumbnail">
                          <img src="../img/RooftopRendering.jpg" alt="">
                          <figcaption style="text-align:right; font-style:italic">
                              Visualization of the Rooftop Building positioned on a pre-existing building (source: Team Rooftop)
                          </figcaption>
                      </div>
                  </div>

                  <p>"Team Rooftop" won 4th place overall and 3rd place in the "Architecture" competition.</p>

                    <div class="col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
                        <div class="thumbnail">
                            <img src="../img/Rooftop_Versailles.jpg" alt="">
                            <figcaption style="text-align:right; font-style:italic">
                                Members of "Team Rooftop" in 2014 at the competition in Versailles (source: Team Rooftop)
                            </figcaption>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                <p>The research building was reconstructed in 2017 on the campus of the UdK in Berlin-Charlottenburg
                (Location: <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/dJ7eZqmw2pLDzRLL8">Einsteinufer 43-53, 10587 Berlin</a>, right next to the main administrative building of the UdK Berlin). It is now being used by both the UdK Berlin and the TU Berlin for
                research and teaching. Various aspects of building operation
                (indoor climate, building technology, energy balance, occupant behavior) are being monitored long-term.</p>

                  <div class="col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
                      <div class="thumbnail">
                          <img src="../img/Rooftop_Einsteinufer.jpg" alt="">
                          <figcaption style="text-align:right; font-style:italic">
                              Rooftop Building rebuilt at Einsteinufer 43-53 (source: UdK Berlin)
                          </figcaption>
                      </div>
                  </div>

                  <p>The building currently serves as a living laboratory for the development and testing of Smart-Building Technologies,
                  the examination of occupant behavior, and the development of algorithms for efficient building energy management.</p>
